es":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ibm-skills-network/mark/issues/327/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"not_planned","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/graphql/issues/4006","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/graphql","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/graphql/issues/4006/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/graphql/issues/4006/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/graphql/issues/4006/events","html_url":"https://github.com/nestjs/graphql/issues/4006","id":4487497968,"node_id":"I_kwDOBtFoEs8AAAABC3nI8A","number":4006,"title":"PickType with ObjectType decorator on dual-decorated parent produces empty InputType in 13.4.0+","user":{"login":"greenreign","id":3790315,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM3OTAzMTU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3790315?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/greenreign","html_url":"https://github.com/greenreign","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/greenreign/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/greenreign/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/greenreign/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/greenreign/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/greenreign/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/greenreign/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/greenreign/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/greenreign/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/greenreign/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-20T14:50:30Z","updated_at":"2026-05-21T07:34:43Z","closed_at":"2026-05-21T07:34:43Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Bug Report\n\n### Description\n\nWhen a class is decorated with both `@InputType()` and `@ObjectType()`, using `PickType` to create a child class that is also dual-decorated causes schema generation to fail in **13.4.0+**.\n\n`PickType` now only registers fields for **one** decorator type. Depending on which arg you pass, a different side ends up empty:\n\n- `PickType(Parent, [...], ObjectType)` → ObjectType gets fields, InputType is empty:\n  ```\n  GraphQLError: Input Object type Child must define one or more fields.\n  ```\n- `PickType(Parent, [...])` (no arg) → InputType gets fields, ObjectType is empty:\n  ```\n  GraphQLError: Type ChildObject must define one or more fields.\n  ```\n\nRemoving the `ObjectType` arg does **not** fix the issue — it just shifts the error to the other side.\n\n### Minimal Repro\n\n**Full repro repository:** https://github.com/greenreign/nestjs-graphql-picktype-repro\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/greenreign/nestjs-graphql-picktype-repro\ncd nestjs-graphql-picktype-repro\nnpm install\nnpm start  # fails with schema generation error\n```\n\n**Nested type** — also dual-decorated:\n\n```ts\n@InputType()\n@ObjectType('NestedAObject')\nexport class NestedA extends NestedBase {\n  @Field(() => [String])\n  values!: string[];\n}\n```\n\n**Parent class** — decorated with both `@InputType()` and `@ObjectType()`, nullable fields of complex dual-decorated types:\n\n```ts\n@InputType()\n@ObjectType('ParentObject')\nexport class Parent {\n  @Field({ nullable: true })\n  @Type(() => NestedA)\n  fieldA?: NestedA;\n  // ... other nullable fields\n}\n```\n\n**Child class** — picks one field, also dual-decorated:\n\n```ts\n@InputType()\n@ObjectType('ChildObject')\nexport class Child extends PickType(Parent, ['fieldA'] as const, ObjectType) {}\n```\n\n**Resolver** — `Child` used as both input AND output (required to surface both failure modes):\n\n```ts\n@Query(() => Child, { nullable: true })\nhello(@Args('filter', { type: () => Child, nullable: true }) _filter?: Child): Child | null {\n  return null;\n}\n```\n\n### Failure modes\n\n```ts\n// Fails: Input Object type Child must define one or more fields.\nexport class Child extends PickType(Parent, ['fieldA'] as const, ObjectType) {}\n\n// Also fails: Type ChildObject must define one or more fields.\nexport class Child extends PickType(Parent, ['fieldA'] as const) {}\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBoth failure modes should succeed — the child should have fields registered in both the InputType and ObjectType registries.\n\n### Versions\n\n| `@nestjs/graphql` | Result |\n|---|---|\n| 13.2.4 | ✅ works |\n| 13.4.0 | ❌ fails |\n| 13.4.1 | ❌ fails |\n\n### Root Cause\n\nPR #3959 (\"Stopped double-registering PickType inputs\") intentionally stopped registering PickType fields under both InputType and ObjectType. However, this broke the legitimate use case where a `PickType` child is itself dual-decorated (`@InputType()` + `@ObjectType()`) and needs fields registered in **both** registries.\n\n### Workaround\n\nInline the fields directly instead of using `PickType`:\n\n```ts\n@InputType()\n@ObjectType('ChildObject')\nexport class Child {\n  @Field({ nullable: true })\n  @Type(() => NestedA)\n  fieldA?: NestedA;\n}\n```\n\n### Environment\n\n- `@nestjs/graphql`: 13.4.1\n- `graphql`: 16.x\n- `@nestjs/apollo`: 12.x\n- Node.js: 20.x","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/graphql/issues/4006/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/graphql/issues/4006/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/n