ps://github.com/QusaiAlbonni","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/QusaiAlbonni/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/QusaiAlbonni/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/QusaiAlbonni/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/QusaiAlbonni/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/QusaiAlbonni/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/QusaiAlbonni/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/QusaiAlbonni/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/QusaiAlbonni/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/QusaiAlbonni/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":1372168894,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxMzcyMTY4ODk0","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/labels/needs%20triage","name":"needs triage","color":"ffffff","default":false,"description":"This issue has not been looked into"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2026-05-05T20:32:56Z","updated_at":"2026-05-06T11:39:01Z","closed_at":"2026-05-06T11:39:01Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":{"id":6039225,"node_id":"IT_kwDOAbL7m84AXCa5","name":"Bug","description":"An unexpected problem or behavior","color":"red","created_at":"2024-01-30T14:06:35Z","updated_at":"2024-07-26T11:37:18Z","is_enabled":true},"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Is there an existing issue for this?\n\n- [x] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### Current behavior\n\nWhen using FileTypeValidator in NestJS with diskStorage (from multer), uploaded files often do not contain a buffer property.\n\nIn this case:\n\n- file.buffer is undefined\n- fallbackToMimetype is false (default)\n- isValid() returns false early due to missing buffer\n\nHowever, the error message generated by buildErrorMessage() assumes the failure is due to MIME type mismatch:\n`Validation failed (current file type is image/jpeg, expected type is /(image\\\\/jpeg|image\\\\/jpg|image\\\\/png)$/)`\n## How the issue manifests\n\n- The validation fails correctly due to missing buffer\n- But the error message incorrectly suggests a MIME type mismatch\n- This leads to misleading debugging information for users using diskStorage\n- There is no indication that the failure was caused by absence of in-memory file data\n\n## Impact\n\n- Confusing error diagnosis when using diskStorage\n- Misleading assumption that file type is incorrect\n- No visibility into actual validation failure reason (missing buffer case)\n\n### Minimum reproduction code\n\nhttps://github.com/QusaiAlbonni/nest-filetypevalidator-misleading-message-reproduce\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `npm ci`\n2. `npx nest start`\n3. use your http client and add a file with its key as 'file' and a jpeg or png file as a value, example with curl:\n`curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/upload -F \"file=@/path/to/test.jpg\"`\nyou will see a misleading error message about mimetypes\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen file.buffer is missing and fallbackToMimetype is false:\n\n- The error message should reflect the actual cause of failure\n- It should not incorrectly suggest a MIME type mismatch\n\n## **Suggested improvement**\n### Option 1: explicit handling of missing buffer\n\nWe could add a check in buildErrorMessage() for missing buffer:\n```ts\nif (!file?.buffer && !this.validationOptions?.fallbackToMimetype) {\n  return 'Validation failed (file buffer is not available; cannot perform file type validation)';\n}\n```\n### Option 2: Add a note or warning in documentations:\nif this behavior and error message is correct and intended we could add a note in the documentation to clarify it.\n\n\n### NestJS version\n\n11.1.19\n\n### Packages versions\n\n[System Information]\nOS Version     : Linux 6.17.0-22-generic\nNodeJS Version : v24.14.1\nNPM Version    : 11.11.0 \n\n[Nest CLI]\nNest CLI Version : 11.0.21 \n\n[Nest Platform Information]\nplatform-express version : 11.1.19\nschematics version       : 11.1.0\ntesting version          : 11.1.19\ncommon version           : 11.1.19\ncore version             : 11.1.19\ncli version              : 11.0.21\n\n\n### Node.js version\n\n24.14.1\n\n### In which operating systems have you tested?\n\n- [ ] macOS\n- [ ] Windows\n- [x] Linux\n\n### Other\n\n_No response_","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16892/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16892/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16927","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16927/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16927/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16927/events","html_url":"https://github.com/nestjs/nest/issues/16927","id":4423965005,"node_id":"I_kwDOBNMhFM8AAAABB7BZTQ","number":16927,"title":"Detect ambiguous route shadowing and optionally support specificity-based registration","user":{"login":"MarwanRadwan7","id":73190211,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjczMTkwMjEx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/73190211?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/MarwanRadwan7","html_url":"https://github.com/MarwanRadwan7","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MarwanRadwan7/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MarwanRadwan7/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MarwanRadwan7/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MarwanRadwan7/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MarwanRadwan7/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MarwanRadwan7/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MarwanRadwan7/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MarwanRadwan7/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MarwanRadwan7/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":532263510,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw1MzIyNjM1MTA=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/labels/type:%20enhancement%20:wolf:","name":"type: enhancement :wolf:","color":"84b6eb","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2026-05-11T20:13:07Z","updated_at":"2026-05-18T08:43:19Z","closed_at":"2026-05-18T08:43:19Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":{"id":6039227,"node_id":"IT_kwDOAbL7m84AXCa7","name":"Feature","description":"A request, idea, or new functionality","color":"blue","created_at":"2024-01-30T14:06:35Z","updated_at":"2024-10-08T12:30:34Z","is_enabled":true},"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Is there an existing issue that is already proposing this?\n\n- [x] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe it\n\nNest currently discovers controller methods and registers HTTP routes in declaration order. In order-sensitive adapters such as the default Express adapter, this means a parametric route like `@Get(':id')` can silently shadow a more specific route like `@Get('me')` if it is declared first.\n\nThis is difficult to notice because startup succeeds, there is no warning, and the problem only appears at runtime when a request is dispatched to the wrong handler. It is also easy to assume that parameter pipes such as `ParseIntPipe` or DTO validation will constrain matching, but those run after routing has already selected a handler.\n\nThere is already related discussion in #13104, but that request focused on changing matching behavior globally. This proposal is narrower and aims to add guardrails without breaking existing applications.\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like\n\nI would like Nest core to add route-shadowing diagnostics, and optionally an opt-in specificity-based registration strategy for order-sensitive adapters.\n\nA concrete shape could be:\n- Detect overlapping routes during HTTP route registration after module path, controller path, method path, host, version, and global prefix have been composed.\n- Expose a policy such as `routeConflictPolicy: 'off' | 'warn' | 'error'`.\n- Optionally expose `routeResolutionStrategy: 'declaration' | 'specificity'`, defaulting to `declaration` for backward compatibility.\n\nFor example, when Nest sees `GET /users/:id` and `GET /users/me`, it could warn or throw that the static route may be shadowed by the parametric route under the current registration order. If an opt-in `specificity` strategy is enabled, Nest could register static routes before generic param routes for adapters where order matters.\n\n### Teachability, documentation, adoption, migration strategy\n\nThis would be easy to teach because it maps to a common developer expectation: static routes are more specific than param routes.\n\nSuggested docs addition:\n- Add a short “Route precedence and shadowing” section to the controllers/routing docs.\n- Explicitly document that parameter pipes and validation do not affect route selection.\n- Show the common pitfall:\n\n```ts\n@Get(':id')\nfindOne() {}\n\n@Get('me')\nfindMe() {}\n```\n\n### What is the motivation / use case for changing the behavior?\n\n\nThe main motivation is to prevent silent routing bugs.\n\nConcrete use cases:\n\n- Auth/profile endpoints such as /users/me living next to /users/:id\n- Action endpoints such as /orders/:id/cancel living next to more generic /:type/:id patterns\n- Large codebases where routes are spread across many controllers and modules, making declaration-order coupling hard to see\n- Teams migrating from frameworks with typed or ranked routing who assume Nest has similar guardrails","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16927/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16927/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16785","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16785/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16785/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16785/events","html_url":"https://github.com/nestjs/nest/issues/16785","id":4264479581,"node_id":"I_kwDOBNMhFM7-Lstd","number":16785,"title":"@nestjs/cli 11.0.19 SWC build preserves src in output when rootDir is set","user":{"login":"GNURub","id":1318648,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzMTg2NDg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1318648?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/GNURub","html_url":"https://github.com/GNURub","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GNURub/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GNURub/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GNURub/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GNURub/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GNURub/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GNURub/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GNURub/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GNURub/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GNURub/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":532263508,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw1MzIyNjM1MDg=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/labels/type:%20bug%20:sob:","name":"type: bug :sob:","color":"ee0701","default":false,"description":""},{"id":1372168894,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxMzcyMTY4ODk0","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/labels/needs%20triage","name":"needs triage","color":"ffffff","default":false,"description":"This issue has not been looked into"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2026-04-14T20:11:57Z","updated_at":"2026-05-04T11:14:16Z","closed_at":"2026-04-15T10:06:55Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":{"id":6039225,"node_id":"IT_kwDOAbL7m84AXCa5","name":"Bug","description":"An unexpected problem or behavior","color":"red","created_at":"2024-01-30T14:06:35Z","updated_at":"2024-07-26T11:37:18Z","is_enabled":true},"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Did you read the migration guide?\n\n- [x] I have read the whole migration guide\n\n### Is there an existing issue that is already proposing this?\n\n- [x] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### Potential Commit/PR that introduced the regression\n\n_No response_\n\n### NestJS version\n\n>11.0.17-\n\n### Describe the regression\n\n## Bug Report: SWC builder emits output to `dist/src/` instead of `dist/`\n\n### Current Behavior\n\nWhen using `@nestjs/cli@11.0.19` with the `swc` builder, the build output changes from:\n\n```text\ndist/main.js\n```\n\nto:\n\n```text\ndist/src/main.js\n```\n\nwhen `tsconfig.build.json` defines `rootDir` as `./src`.\n\nThis breaks projects that expect the compiled entrypoint at `dist/main.js`.\n\n---\n\n### Minimum Reproduction\n\n**`nest-cli.json`**\n```json\n{\n  \"$schema\": \"https://json.schemastore.org/nest-cli\",\n  \"collection\": \"@nestjs/schematics\",\n  \"sourceRoot\": \"src\",\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"builder\": \"swc\",\n    \"deleteOutDir\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**`tsconfig.build.json`**\n```json\n{\n  \"extends\": \"./tsconfig.json\",\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Project structure**\n\n      src/\n          main.ts\n          app.module.ts\n          nest-cli.json\n          tsconfig.json\n          tsconfig.build.json\n\n**Build command**\n```bash\nnest build\n```\n\n---\n\n### Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Create a NestJS app using the `swc` builder\n2. Set `sourceRoot` to `src` in `nest-cli.json`\n3. Set `rootDir` to `./src` and `outDir` to `./dist` in `tsconfig.build.json`\n4. Run `nest build`\n\n\n### Actual Behavior\n\nOutput is emitted under `dist/src/`:\n      dist/src/main.js\n      dist/src/app.module.js\n---\n\n### Environment\n\n| | |\n|---|---|\n| `@nestjs/cli` | `11.0.19` |\n| Builder | `swc` |\n| Node.js | `24.11.1` |\n| OS | Linux |\n\n\n### Minimum reproduction code\n\n_No response_\n\n### Input code\n\n```ts\n\n```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n\n## Output should be emitted directly under `dist/`:\n\n      dist/main.js\n      dist/app.module.js\n\n### Other\n\n_No response_","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16785/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nestjs/nest/issues/16785/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp/issues/283","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp/issues/283/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp/issues/283/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp/issues/283/events","html_url":"https://github.com/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp/issues/283","id":4414063039,"node_id":"I_kwDORLwbhM8AAAABBxlBvw","number":283,"title":"Investigate NestJS persistent coupling=4.4 — real finding or measurement bug?","user":{"login":"jgravelle","id":3400540,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0MDA1NDA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3400540?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jgravelle","html_url":"https://github.com/jgravelle","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jgravelle/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jgravelle/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jgravelle/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jgravelle/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jgravelle/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jgravelle/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jgravelle/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jgravelle/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jgravelle/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10165453138,"node_id":"LA_kwDORLwbhM8AAAACXeiBUg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp/labels/question","name":"question","color":"d876e3","default":true,"description":"Further information is requested"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-09T22:58:55Z","updated_at":"2026-05-09T23:45:48Z","closed_at":"2026-05-09T23:45:48Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Background\n\nAfter v1.91.0 (dir filter) and v1.92.0 (filename filter) shipped,\nthe observatory shows NestJS at:\n\n- composite = **77.2 (C)**\n- **coupling axis = 4.4** ← unchanged through both releases\n- total_files = 1,944\n- repo: https://github.com/nestjs/nest\n\nDecoding the coupling score: `4.4 = 100 - 200 * ratio` → ratio =\n**47.8%**. After excluding `tests/`, `test/`, `*.spec.ts`, and\n`*.test.ts`, roughly **half** of what we count as production files\nin NestJS are still flagged with instability > 0.7 (Ce-dominated).\n\nThat number is suspiciously high for a real production codebase\nof this maturity. Worth a closer look.\n\n## Two hypotheses\n\n### A. Real architectural finding\n\nNestJS is a Lerna-style monorepo: `packages/core`, `packages/common`,\n`packages/microservices`, `packages/platform-express`, `packages/platform-fastify`,\n`packages/testing`, etc. Cross-package imports are extensive by\ndesign. Every `packages/<X>/src/foo.ts` that imports from\n`packages/<Y>/src/bar.ts` adds Ce, and unless `<Y>`'s file gets\nimported back, it shows as Ce-dominated.\n\nIf this hypothesis is right, the score is honest: NestJS's\ninter-package fan-out genuinely produces high instability for many\nfiles, and there's no metric bug to fix.\n\n### B. Measurement bug\n\nThe TypeScript import resolver may not be crediting Ca correctly\nfor monorepo paths. Symptoms to look for:\n\n- TS path aliases (`@nestjs/common` → `packages/common/index.ts`)\n  resolved via `tsconfig.json` `paths` field — does\n  `imports.resolve_specifier` walk those?\n- Barrel files (`index.ts` re-exports) — does the import graph\n  follow re-exports, or does it stop at the immediate alias?\n- `package.json` `exports` field — TS 4.7+ uses this for monorepo\n  internal resolution; may not be in our resolver.\n\nIf any of these are missing, then real Ca relationships are being\ndropped, files look more Ce-dominated than they are, and the score\nis artificially low.\n\n## Suggested investigation steps\n\n1. Pick a known-good NestJS file with many internal callers (e.g.\n   `packages/common/decorators/core/injectable.decorator.ts` —\n   `@Injectable()` is used everywhere).\n2. Run `find_importers` against it. Compare the result with what\n   `grep -r \"@Injectable\" packages/` returns.\n3. If the import-graph result is much smaller than the grep result,\n   that's evidence for hypothesis B — the resolver is missing\n   real edges.\n4. Check whether `imports.resolve_specifier` honors `tsconfig.json`\n   `paths` in `vscode-extension/`-style monorepos vs root-level\n   ones.\n\n## Acceptance criteria for closing this issue\n\nEither:\n\n- [ ] Confirm hypothesis A (real architectural finding) — document\n      that NestJS-style monorepos are *expected* to score low on\n      coupling, no action; or\n- [ ] Identify and fix the resolver gap that's dropping monorepo\n      Ca edges; observatory rebuild shows NestJS coupling rises\n      meaningfully.\n\n## Why this is backlog, not P0\n\nThe score is stable (not regressing), the rest of the radar reports\ncorrectly, and other monorepo repos in the observatory aren't\nshowing the same pattern. Worth investigating but not blocking any\nrelease.\n\n## Related\n\n- v1.91.0 ([PR #279](https://github.com/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp/pull/279))\n  — coupling axis: dir filter\n- v1.92.0 ([PR #282](https://github.com/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp/pull/282))\n  — coupling axis: filename filter (closed [#280](https://github.com/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp/issues/280))\n\n-jjg","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp/issues/283/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jgravelle/jcodemunch-mcp/issues/2